      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:3:32:1",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ اللَّهَ احْتَجَّ عَلَى النَّاسِ بِمَا آتَاهُمْ وَ عَرَّفَهُمْ .",
        "مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ إِسْمَاعِيلَ عَنِ الْفَضْلِ بْنِ شَاذَانَ عَنِ ابْنِ أَبِي عُمَيْرٍ عَنْ جَمِيلِ بْنِ دَرَّاجٍ مِثْلَهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, and someone else, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Al Husayn Bin Saeed, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Jameel Bin Darraj, from Ibn Al Tayyar, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Argued upon the people with what He<sup>azwj</sup> Gave them and Introduced them (to)’. ",
          "<span style=\"font-size: small\">Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Al Fazl Bin Shazan, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Jameel Bin Darraj </span>– similar to it."
        ]
      }
    },
